Chiloé &ldquo;So, what next?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Well, we will go to Chiloé. And it will be good.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I thought we were already in Chile?&rdquo;
I was, by now, used to this kind of total, brutish ignorance. After all, my brother had spent the previous two weeks insisting he could speak Spanish by adding dado to the end of English words. And this from a scientist! At any rate, it didn&rsquo;t matter much, the big man had long since given up creative control over the trip to his reclusive younger brother, and a twenty year out of date Lonely Planet guide to Chile.
